{% for s in lastSpeakers %}
- {{ s }}
{% endfor %}

**Recent banter pairs (most recent at the bottom):**
{% for p in lastPairs %}
- {{ p }}
{% endfor %}

**Hard rotation rule (read this carefully):**
1. Look at the LAST entry in "Recent speakers" — that follower CANNOT be the speaker this turn. Pick a different speaker (swap roles within the pair if needed).
2. If a single follower's name appears in the last 3 speaker entries, that follower CANNOT speak again — force a different opener.
{% if followerCount >= 3 %}
3. Look at the LAST entry in "Recent banter pairs" — that exact pair (in either order) CANNOT banter this turn. Pick a different pair, even if it means lower affinity.
4. If only one pair is eligible after these filters and they just bantered, output {"banter":null}. Silence is preferable to repetition.
{% else %}
3. (Pair rotation skipped — only {{ followerCount }} follower(s) present, so the same pair is the only option. Vary the speaker and the topic instead, and lean toward silence more often than usual so this same pair isn't trading lines every tick.)
{% endif %}
{% else %}
No recent banters on record — any pair is fair game. Pick the most thematically interesting pair, not just the highest-affinity one.
{% endif %}

